"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418973","Department of Health","false","2015-09-21","<p>There are no figures available for prisoners addicted to heroin.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2015-09-21T16:12:56.763Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418973/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418973/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418973/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-09-15","Prisons: Heroin","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many prisoners in what age groups were addicted to heroin in the most recent period for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","10259"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418974","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-09-30","<p /> <p>In January this year, as part of our probation reforms we introduced a new tool which sees all new offenders entering prison asked if they have served in the Armed Forces. Prior to this information on ex-armed service personnel in prisons was not held centrally.</p><p> </p><p>We intend to publish this information at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/offender-management-statistics-quarterly" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/offender-management-statistics-quarterly</a> from January 2016, subject to appropriate quality assurance checks having been carried out.</p>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous",,"2015-09-30T09:48:39.563Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418974/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418974/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418974/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-09-15","Prisoners: Veterans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what estimate he has made of the number of ex-army personnel who are serving a prison sentence for a minor offence in the most recent period for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","10260"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418975","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-10-12","<p>The latest statistics relating to foreign national offenders in custody in England and Wales are published in <em>Prison population: April to June 2015, table 1.6</em> which can be found at the link below.</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/offender-management-statistics-quarterly-january-to-march-2015" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/offender-management-statistics-quarterly-january-to-march-2015</a></p><p>The number of convicted foreign national offenders serving their sentence outside prison is not published due to data quality.</p>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous",,"2015-10-12T09:19:17.343Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418975/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418975/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418975/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-09-15","Offenders: Foreign Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many convicted foreign national offenders are serving their sentence (a) in and (b) outside prison.","false","Biography information for Mr Philip Hollobone","Kettering","Mr Philip Hollobone","10247"
