"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418977","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-10-12","<p>We do not hold this information centrally.</p><p>Information about independent appeals services is provided by the British Parking Association and the Independent Parking Committee. They also publish a code of practice which governs the operation of the appeals services.</p><p>There are a number of other organisations which provde advice to motorists on parking such as the Citizens Advice Bureau.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones","10245","2015-10-12T14:37:36.397Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418977/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418977/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418977/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-09-15","Parking Offences","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many parking penalty charge notices issued by a private firm have been successfully appealed where the registered keeper has proved that a notice was (a) not sent by a private parking company and (b) not received by the registered keeper in the last year for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Mr David Nuttall","Bury North","Mr David Nuttall","10289"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418978","Department for Transport","false","2015-09-23","<p>The Department does not hold details of the timing, number or value of such payments, which are a commercial matter between the parties directly concerned, overseen by the Office of Rail and Road.</p><p> </p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2015-09-23T08:30:59.377Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418978/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418978/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418978/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-09-15","Great Western Railway Line: Electrification","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what Schedule 4 compensation payments have been made by Network Rail to train operators on the Great Western Mainline as a result of electrification of the line.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Edwards","Carmarthen East and Dinefwr","Jonathan Edwards","10378"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418979","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-10-12","<p>We are currently conducting a review of off-street parking policy. A discussion paper entitled ‘Parking reform: tackling unfair practices was’ published earlier this year. We received in excess of 500 detailed responses to the discussion paper where the issue of burden of proof being on the registered keeper was raised. We are currently considering this issue as we develop policy options, and will publish a response in due course.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones","10246","2015-10-12T14:24:52.337Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418979/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418979/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418979/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-09-15","Parking Offences","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, if he will publish guidance on how a registered vehicle keeper can provide evidence that an item of post they were not expecting has not been received so that they can comply with the provisions of Schedule 4 of the Protection of Freedoms Act 2012.","false","Biography information for Mr David Nuttall","Bury North","Mr David Nuttall","10288"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418980","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-10-12","<p>We do not hold this information centrally.</p><p>Information about independent appeals services is provided by the British Parking Association and the Independent Parking Committee. They also publish a code of practice which governs the operation of the appeals services.</p><p>There are a number of other organisations which provde advice to motorists on parking such as the Citizens Advice Bureau.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones","10289","2015-10-12T14:37:36.287Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418980/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418980/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418980/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-09-15","Parking Offences","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what assistance is available, from which bodies, to registered keepers of a vehicle who wish to dispute a parking penalty charge and under schedule 4 of the Protection of Freedoms Act 2012 must prove that the initial penalty charge notice issued by a private parking company was not received by post.","false","Biography information for Mr David Nuttall","Bury North","Mr David Nuttall","10245"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418981","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-10-12","<p>We are currently conducting a review of off-street parking policy. A discussion paper entitled ‘Parking reform: tackling unfair practices was’ published earlier this year. We received in excess of 500 detailed responses to the discussion paper where the issue of burden of proof being on the registered keeper was raised. We are currently considering this issue as we develop policy options, and will publish a response in due course.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones","10288","2015-10-12T14:24:52.257Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418981/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418981/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418981/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-09-15","Parking Offences","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, if he will amend schedule 4 of the Protection of Freedoms Act 2012 so that it does not place a burden of proof on a registered keeper of a vehicle to provide evidence that a parking penalty charge notice issued by a private firm was not received by post.","false","Biography information for Mr David Nuttall","Bury North","Mr David Nuttall","10246"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418982","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-10-12","<p>The information requested is not collated centrally and could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-10-12T14:13:42.73Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418982/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418982/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418982/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-09-15","Social Security Benefits: Brighton","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people received an assessment for both employment and support allowance and personal independence payment in (a) 2014 and (b) the first six months of 2015 in Brighton and Hove local authority area.","false","Biography information for Peter Kyle","Hove","Peter Kyle","10287"
