"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418984","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-09-17","<p /> <p>22,460 households were subject to the benefit cap as at May 2015 and of these, 10,170 households (45%) also had their benefits capped at February 2014.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-09-17T14:21:00.03Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418984/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418984/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418984/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-09-15","Social Security Benefits","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many of the households affected by the benefit cap in May 2015 were also affected by that cap in February 2014.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","10241"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418985","HM Treasury","false","2015-09-23","<p>This information is unavailable.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Government is making changes to Tax Credits and Universal Credit which will help put welfare spending on a more sustainable path. The emphasis is on supporting hardworking families on low incomes by reducing income tax through increases in the personal allowance and increasing wages, rather than on topping up low wages through tax credits.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>HMT has published a distributional analysis of the impact of the Summer Budget 2015 which includes the effect of tax credit and other welfare measures on households. This information can be found here:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/443229/PU1822_Distributional_Analysis.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/443229/PU1822_Distributional_Analysis.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>HMRC publishes information on families’ tax credit awards within local authorities. The most recent available data is for 2013-14 and can be found here:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/personal-tax-credits-finalised-award-statistics-geographical-statistics-2013-to-2014" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/personal-tax-credits-finalised-award-statistics-geographical-statistics-2013-to-2014</a></p><p> </p><p>Information on the number of families in individual constituencies receiving tax credits and the average value of these payments can be found in table 2.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2015-09-23T12:57:20.027Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418985/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418985/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418985/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-09-15","Welfare Tax Credits","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many families in each constituency will be affected by the Tax Credits (Income Thresholds and Determination of Rates) (Amendment) Regulations 2015.","false","Biography information for Greg Mulholland","Leeds North West","Greg Mulholland","10377"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418986","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-09-23","<p /> <p>A total of 5,100 work capability assessments were carried out in Inverclyde; 221,900 in Scotland, and; 1,914,000 in Britain between April 2013 and March 2015. All figures are rounded to the nearest hundred. The assessments include Employment and Support Allowance initial assessments, repeat assessments and Incapacity Benefit reassessments.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-09-23T11:06:37.853Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418986/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418986/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418986/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-09-15","Employment and Support Allowance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many work capability assessments in connection with claims for employment and support allowance have been carried out in (a) Inverclyde, (b) Scotland and (c) the UK in the last two years.","false","Biography information for Ronnie Cowan","Inverclyde","Ronnie Cowan","10296"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418987","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-09-23","<p>Inverclyde is part of our Tranche 3 roll out schedule which runs from September 2015 to November 2015 and goes live on 12 October 2015.</p><p> </p><p>More information can be found at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/414937/universal-credit-national-expansion-tranche-three-and-four.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/414937/universal-credit-national-expansion-tranche-three-and-four.pdf</a></p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-09-23T11:01:39.427Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418987/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418987/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418987/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-09-15","Universal Credit: Inverclyde","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, when universal credit will be rolled out in Inverclyde constituency.","false","Biography information for Ronnie Cowan","Inverclyde","Ronnie Cowan","10297"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418988","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-09-21","<p /> <p>Statistical information regarding the habitual residence test is intended for publication at a future date.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-09-21T11:35:13.293Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418988/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418988/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418988/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-09-15","Jobseeker's Allowance: Habitual Residence Test","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many UK citizens have been unsuccessful in claiming jobseeker's allowance since January 2014 because they did not meet the criteria for the habitual residence test.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","10298"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418989","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-09-17","<p /> <p>The Department has no plans to publish the benefit type administrative data prior to May 2015.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-09-17T14:25:30.677Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418989/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418989/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418989/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-09-15","Social Security Benefits","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the Answer of 9 September 2015 to Question 8871, on data or categories of households affected by the benefit cap, if he will publish that administrative data on people claiming each benefit prior to May 2015.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","10283"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418990","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-09-23","<p>The new statutory child maintenance scheme (“the 2012 Scheme” - administered by the Child Maintenance Service) has a number of key features designed to ensure that non-resident parents meet their financial responsibilities to their children. <br></p><p>For example, the 2012 Scheme uses tax data taken directly from Her Majesty’s Revenue and Customs, addressing challenges around ensuring that the child maintenance calculation is based on accurate earnings information. The scheme also enables swifter identification and follow-up of those non-resident parents who fail to pay their child maintenance. <br></p><p>Where non-resident parents fail to meet their liabilities, there are a range of enforcement powers; for example, child maintenance can be taken directly from bank accounts and wages; non-resident parents are subject to charges for any enforcement action taken against them; and the Government has also introduced a new power to disclose non-compliance to credit reference agencies.</p><p> </p><p>Note:</p><p> </p><p>The Department for Work and Pensions is responsible for the Child Maintenance Service in Great Britain, in Northern Ireland Child Maintenance is administered by the Department for Social Development.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-09-23T12:25:34.097Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418990/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418990/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418990/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-09-15","Children: Maintenance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what steps his Department takes to ensure that absentee fathers are financially responsible for their dependent children.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","10282"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418991","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-09-17","<p /> <p>DWP does not have contractual pay progression. The value and method of any progression forms part of the annual pay review and must be affordable within the terms set out in the annual civil service pay guidance issued by Treasury.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-09-17T15:24:08.587Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418991/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418991/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418991/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-09-15","Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what his policy is on limits to progression pay increases for civil servants in his Department.","false","Biography information for Mr Nicholas Brown","Newcastle upon Tyne East","Mr Nicholas Brown","10329"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418992","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-09-22","<p /> <p>In the unlikely event that this occurred, the determination could be subject to judicial review in the High Court. A Pension Ombudsman's determination can also be challenged on a point of law in the High Court.</p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-09-22T15:21:46.34Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418992/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418992/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418992/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-09-15","Pensions Ombudsman: Appeals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what procedures are in place for challenges to Pension Ombudsman decisions based on false information having been provided to the Ombudsman.","false","Biography information for Holly Lynch","Halifax","Holly Lynch","10320"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418993","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-09-18","<p /> <p>The information requested is not available. This is because, as set out in the Impact Assessment of the behavioural effects of the cap; all households who move into work will be unaffected by the changes. Additionally, for many people who will be affected by the cap, these reductions are notional changes in entitlement rather than actual cash losses i.e. those who become capped once the policy is in place will not see a reduction in their benefit, just a lower maximum limit on the benefit they would otherwise have been entitled to.</p><p> </p>","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson",,"2015-09-18T12:16:04.277Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418993/answer","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418993/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418993/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-09-15","Social Security Benefits","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, with reference to page two of the Impact Assessment for the Benefit Cap published on 20 July 2015, how many and what proportion of those affected by the lower cap on the day of its introduction will experience a cash loss.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","10318"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418994","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-10-12","<p>We are in active conversations with the Department of Health about the content of their forms.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel","10360","2015-10-12T14:25:18.377Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418994/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418994/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418994/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-09-15","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, when he expects all NHS charges claim forms to include a box applicable for universal credit.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","10358"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418995","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-10-12","<p>We are in active conversations with the Department of Health about the content of their forms.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel","10358","2015-10-12T14:25:18.437Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418995/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418995/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418995/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-09-15","Universal Credit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many outstanding sanctions and appeals are related to universal credit claimants not ticking the appropriate box on NHS charges claim forms when claiming help with NHS health costs in cases where the claim forms do not include such a box.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","10360"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418996","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2015-10-12","<p>During a Work Capability Assessment there is a requirement to assess both physical and mental health risks. This is covered in the guidance issued to Centre for Health and Disability Assessments (CHDA) healthcare professionals. Specifically, if a claimant indicates suicidal thoughts or intentions this is given careful and sensitive exploration by healthcare professionals to establish the full circumstances. There is a duty of care to act where appropriate, which may in some situations include calling the emergency services if the claimant is considered to be in substantial and imminent risk. If the claimants own GP is not aware then an agreed process is followed to inform the GP to ensure medical attention is provided.</p>","Witham","Priti Patel",,"2015-10-12T16:39:56.83Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418996/answer","Biography information for Priti Patel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418996/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418996/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2015-09-15","Work Capability Assessment: Mental Health","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what requirement there is on an assessor to report that a claimant reports suicidal thoughts or intentions during a work capability assessment.","false","Biography information for Louise Haigh","Sheffield, Heeley","Louise Haigh","10351"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418590","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-09-21","<p>No such assessment has been made. The BBC's proposals published in 'British, Bold, Creative - The BBC’s programmes and services in the next Charter', including its ideas for the future of the World Service, will be an important part of the Charter Review process the Government is running.</p>",,"Baroness Neville-Rolfe",,"2015-09-21T15:54:40.76Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418590/answer","Biography information for Baroness Neville-Rolfe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418590/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418590/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-09-14","BBC World Service: North Korea","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of the BBC’s decision to inaugurate broadcasts to the Korean peninsula.","false","Biography information for Lord Alton of Liverpool",,"Lord Alton of Liverpool","HL2182"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418591","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-10-01","<p>We will announce the Government’s response when we publish the Report on the consultation in the next few weeks.</p><p><br></p>",,"Baroness Neville-Rolfe",,"2015-10-01T14:58:19.267Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418591/answer","Biography information for Baroness Neville-Rolfe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418591/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418591/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-09-14","Packaging","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government when they expect to publish their response to the consultation on the Consumer Protection from Unfair Trading Regulations 2008 regarding misleadingly similar packaging.","false","Biography information for Lord Clement-Jones",,"Lord Clement-Jones","HL2183"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418592","Cabinet Office","false","2015-09-25","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the Charity Commission. I have asked the Chief Executive to reply.</p>",,"Lord Bridges of Headley",,"2015-09-25T12:14:22.53Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418592/answer","Biography information for Lord Bridges of Headley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418592/answer","Baroness Finlay PQ2184.pdf","Baroness Finlay PQ2184.pdf","Charity Commission Reply ","Charity Commission Reply ","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418592/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-09-14","Charity Commission","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how many reports of serious incidents the Charity Commission has received this year; and what is (1) the average, and (2) the maximum, time delay in investigating those reports.","false","Biography information for Baroness Finlay of Llandaff",,"Baroness Finlay of Llandaff","HL2184"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418593","Department of Health","false","2015-09-21","<p>We are committed to implementing these savings in a way which will minimise any impact on services. We consulted from 31 July to 28 August 2015 on the best way of delivering the required savings, which will be applied to local authorities’ public health grant allocations, and are currently considering responses.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p>",,"Lord Prior of Brampton",,"2015-09-21T15:07:24.17Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418593/answer","Biography information for Lord Prior of Brampton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418593/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418593/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-09-14","Health: Finance","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how the proposed £200 million reductions in the public health budget will be distributed; what proportion will be to (1) central funds, and (2) local public health authority funds; by what formula the allocation of spending reductions amongst local authorities is distributed; and what advice they plan to give to local public health authorities about which services or activities should carry the reductions.","false","Biography information for Lord Greaves",,"Lord Greaves","HL2185"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418594","Cabinet Office","false","2015-09-25","<p>The Freedom of Information Act 2000 applies to all information held by a public authority. However the Act contains an exemption that would protect the names, addresses and other personal information within petitions submitted to and held by public authorities.</p>",,"Lord Bridges of Headley",,"2015-09-25T11:54:37.867Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418594/answer","Biography information for Lord Bridges of Headley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418594/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418594/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-09-14","Petitions: Freedom of Information","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether the Freedom of Information Act 2000 applies to the names, addresses and other personal information, in whole or in part, that forms part of a petition that has been delivered to a public authority to which that Act applies.","false","Biography information for Lord Greaves",,"Lord Greaves","HL2186"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418595","Home Office","false","2015-10-08","<p>Since 2011, we have consistently defined extremism as ‘Vocal or active opposition to fundamental British values, including democracy, the rule of law, individual liberty and mutual respect and tolerance of different faiths and beliefs. We also include in our definition of extremism calls for the death of members of our armed forces, whether in this country or overseas’.</p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon",,"2015-10-08T15:34:05.703Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418595/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418595/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418595/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-09-14","Radicalism","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how they define extremism, other than violent extremism, as mentioned in the Statement of 7 September regarding Syria (HL Deb, cols 1246–50).","false","Biography information for Lord Hylton",,"Lord Hylton","HL2187"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418596","Home Office","false","2015-09-28","<p>There are a number of safeguards to ensure that steps taken to stop British terrorism suspects from travelling do not continue to affect them once suspicion has been removed: The return of a passport after a maximum of 30 days where it has been confiscated under Schedule 1 powers; the issue of a passport on application where a passport has previously been withdrawn or refused as a result of the exercise of the Royal Prerogative; and the ability to travel or apply for a passport at the end of a Terrorism Prevention and Investigation Measures notice when it has either expired or been successfully challenged by judicial review.</p>",,"Lord Bates",,"2015-09-28T17:31:30.48Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418596/answer","Biography information for Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418596/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418596/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-09-14","Terrorism: Travel Restrictions","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how they plan to ensure that steps taken to stop British terrorism suspects from travelling do not continue to affect them once the suspicion has been removed.","false","Biography information for Lord Hylton",,"Lord Hylton","HL2188"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418597","Home Office","false","2015-09-17","<p>The Code of Practice on Police Use of Firearms and Less Lethal Weapons 2003, made under section 39A of the Police Act 1996 determines the framework by which police forces use both conventional firearms and less lethal weapons. The Authorised Professional Practice on the Use of Force, Firearms and Less Lethal Weapons clearly states that “only less lethal weapons that have been approved by the Secretary of State may be used by the UK police service.” Water cannon is classed as a less lethal weapon and the Home Secretary’s decision not to authorise its use followed the established authorisation process.</p><p>The deployment of water cannon by police forces in England and Wales is therefore prohibited.</p>",,"Lord Bates","HL2225","2015-09-17T11:39:42.597Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418597/answer","Biography information for Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418597/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418597/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-09-14","Police: Weapons","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what current legal controls are in place to prevent police forces from deploying weapons that are not officially authorised for use by the Home Office.","false","Biography information for Baroness Jones of Moulsecoomb",,"Baroness Jones of Moulsecoomb","HL2189"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418598","Home Office","false","2015-09-24","<p>Sharia councils may be working in a discriminatory and unacceptable way. That is why, as part of the forthcoming Counter-Extremism Strategy, Government will commission a full, independent investigation to assess to what extent Sharia is being applied in a manner that is unacceptable. The review will commence following the appointment of an independent chair. The Terms of Reference for the review and its duration will be determined at that point. We will act on any evidence of it’s application which is outside of the law.</p>",,"Lord Bates",,"2015-09-24T15:46:03.11Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418598/answer","Biography information for Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418598/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418598/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-09-14","Islam: Legal Systems","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government when the undertaking by the Home Secretary, made in a speech on 23 March, to set up an independent investigation into the application of Shari’a law in Britain will be fulfilled; and when that investigation is expected to report.","false","Biography information for The Lord Bishop of St Albans",,"The Lord Bishop of St Albans","HL2190"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418599","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-09-23","<p>The Government is working to improve the diversity and inclusiveness of the construction sector through the Construction Leadership Council (CLC) and the Construction Industry Training Board (CITB). Actions include a new CLC led image and recruitment campaign for the sector, the CITB Fairness Inclusion and Respect initiative and CITB’s work with <em>Be Onsite</em>. More widely we have encouraged industry participation in wider initiatives such as <em>Your Life</em> and <em>Think, Act, Report</em>.</p><p> </p>",,"Baroness Neville-Rolfe",,"2015-09-23T16:11:24.993Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418599/answer","Biography information for Baroness Neville-Rolfe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418599/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418599/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-09-14","Construction: Equality","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what steps they are taking to encourage diversity in the construction and property sectors.","false","Biography information for Lord Taylor of Warwick",,"Lord Taylor of Warwick","HL2191"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418600","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-09-25","<p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p>We believe it is the best interests of business to tap into the richest and widest talent pool.</p><p> </p><p>There are no current plans for any Government led activity to increase the number of board members from ethnic minorities.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>",,"Baroness Neville-Rolfe",,"2015-09-25T12:28:46.807Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418600/answer","Biography information for Baroness Neville-Rolfe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418600/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418600/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-09-14","Directors: Ethnic Groups","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what plans they have to increase the number of board members from ethnic minorities.","false","Biography information for Lord Taylor of Warwick",,"Lord Taylor of Warwick","HL2192"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418601","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-09-28","<p>· LEPs are strategic partnerships made up of business, local authority leaders, and other public sector partners.</p><p> </p><p>· They are accountable for decisions they make, with democratic accountability provided through the local authority leader representation, and financial accountability through each LEP’s accountable local authority, which receive funds on behalf of their LEP.</p><p> </p><p>· To ensure basic accountability standards are upheld, Government has established a set of clear national standards and principles which are set out in the published Accountability Systems Statement for the local growth fund, and the underpinning LEP assurance framework. These standards are broadly equivalent to much of what we expect of local government, building on, rather than duplicating the existing local government framework set out in the Accountability Systems Statement for Local Government and for Fire and Rescue Authorities.</p><p> </p><p>· In line with this national framework, LEPs and their accountable local authorities have put in place local decision making systems to ensure funds are spent with regularity, propriety and value for money. These arrangements are published in each LEP’s own local assurance framework.</p><p> </p><p>· In parallel Government has also developed a coherent approach to the monitoring and evaluation of Growth Deals which LEPs are responsible for. LEPs will report against a range of data on inputs, outputs and outcomes providing clarity to Government and the public about what LEPs have delivered with their Local Growth Fund resources.</p><p> </p><p> </p>",,"Baroness Neville-Rolfe",,"2015-09-28T17:24:37.547Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418601/answer","Biography information for Baroness Neville-Rolfe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418601/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418601/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-09-14","Local Enterprise Partnerships","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what steps they are taking to make local enterprise partnerships more accountable, without duplicating the work of local authorities.","false","Biography information for Lord Taylor of Warwick",,"Lord Taylor of Warwick","HL2193"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418602","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-09-28","<p>We understand the pressures faced by small business owners. This year we launched Fit for Work. While primarily aimed at helping employers with employees who are facing long term sickness absence, the self-employed can access free, impartial work related health advice through the advice element of the scheme. Fit for Work is a free service which provides both a supportive occupational health assessment and general health and work advice to employees, employers and General Practitioners (GPs), to help individuals stay in or return to work.</p><p> </p><p>We are committed to making it easier for small business owners to run their business. We are helping small businesses access the finance they need to startup and grow with British Business Bank programmes already supporting £2.3 billion of finance to 40,000 smaller businesses. Small businesses have less regulation to follow, with savings to businesses of £10bn of red tape in the last Parliament, and have better access to business advice and support through GREATbusiness.gov.uk. The ‘My Business Support Tool’ helps businesses find the support they need quickly, and businesses can speak to or webchat with a helpline adviser direct using our Business Support helpline. Going forward, we have announced a new Small Business Commissioner to help small businesses to settle disputes and challenge unfair payment terms.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>",,"Baroness Neville-Rolfe",,"2015-09-28T17:33:02.877Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418602/answer","Biography information for Baroness Neville-Rolfe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418602/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418602/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-09-14","Small Businesses: Stress","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, in the light of the findings of the recent survey by insurance provider Simply Business, how they plan to support small business owners who have fallen ill due to stress and overwork.","false","Biography information for Lord Taylor of Warwick",,"Lord Taylor of Warwick","HL2194"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418603","Department for International Development","false","2015-09-23","<p>The UK has been supporting the United Nations Relief and Works Agency for Palestine Refugees in the Near East’s (UNRWA) to ensure that the needs of highly vulnerable Palestinians are addressed inside Syria and in neighbouring countries. To date, the UK has allocated over £38 million to UNRWA to provide food parcels, relief items, hygiene packs, education and cash assistance for Palestinian refugees affected by the violence in Syria and the region. This includes £5 million of un-earmarked funding towards UNRWA’s appeal in Syria in 2015, which allows UNRWA to allocate funding to priority areas.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>In August 2015, UNRWA was able to provide basic healthcare in Yalda on four occasions, treating 54 suspected cases of typhoid. UNRWA also distributed 400,000 water purification tablets provided by UNICEF.</p><p> </p>",,"Baroness Verma",,"2015-09-23T15:33:19.7Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418603/answer","Biography information for Baroness Verma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418603/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418603/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2015-09-14","Syria: Refugees","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what action they are taking regarding the increase in reported cases of typhoid amongst Palestinian refugees in Syria.","false","Biography information for Baroness Tonge",,"Baroness Tonge","HL2195"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418604","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-09-24","<p>While we have not raised the issue of neonatal mortality in the Gaza Strip with either the Palestinian Authority or the Israeli authorities, as part of our long-term assistance for Gaza, the UK supports partners like the World Food Programme, the UN Works and Relief Agency and the International Committee of the Red Cross, who help deal with food shortages, provide basic services and repair water infrastructure in Gaza. On 10 September the Prime Minister, my right hon. Friend the Member for Witney (Mr Cameron), emphasised to Israeli Prime Minister Netanyahu the importance of improving daily life for the people of Gaza.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2015-09-24T15:33:23.307Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418604/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418604/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418604/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-09-14","Gaza: Neonatal Mortality","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what representations they have made to the Palestinian Authority and the government of Israel regarding the increase in neonatal mortality in the Gaza Strip.","false","Biography information for Baroness Tonge",,"Baroness Tonge","HL2196"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418605","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-09-24","<p>On 10 September the Prime Minister, my right hon. Friend the Member for Witney (Mr Cameron), emphasised to Israeli Prime Minister Netanyahu the importance of improving daily life for the people of Gaza, for example through better power and water supplies and facilitating travel in and out of Gaza. During his visit to the region in July, the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, my right hon. Friend the Member for Runnymede and Weybridge (Mr Hammond), urged the Israeli government to ease restrictions on Gaza and for the parties to prioritise progress towards a durable solution, including taking the necessary steps to advance construction and economic development. Our Embassy in Tel Aviv has also frequently urged Israel to go further in easing movement and access restrictions on Gaza.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2015-09-24T15:33:35.077Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418605/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418605/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418605/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-09-14","Gaza: Israel","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what representations they have made to the government of Israel regarding the block on exports from Gaza.","false","Biography information for Baroness Tonge",,"Baroness Tonge","HL2197"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418606","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-09-24","<p>British Embassy officials discussed this issue with Israel's Ministry of Education during the summer.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2015-09-24T15:38:04.073Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418606/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418606/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418606/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-09-14","Israel: Church Schools","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what discussions they have had with the government of Israel following the strike at Christian schools in Israel in protest against funding cuts.","false","Biography information for Baroness Tonge",,"Baroness Tonge","HL2198"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418607","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-09-24","<p>Officials from our Embassy in Tel Aviv raised the issue of the investigation with the Israeli Defence Minister on 10 September. We have called on the Israeli authorities to ensure that those responsible for this crime are brought swiftly to justice.</p><p> </p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2015-09-24T15:39:07.043Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418607/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418607/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418607/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-09-14","West Bank: Arson","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what representations they have made to the government of Israel concerning the lack of progress in arresting the people responsible for the Duma village arson attack in July 2015.","false","Biography information for Baroness Tonge",,"Baroness Tonge","HL2199"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418608","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-09-24","<p>Our Consul-General in Jerusalem visited the village of Duma on 4 August to express our condolences to the relatives of the Dawabsha family and the local community. On 31 July, the Parliamentary Under-Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, my hon. Friend the Member for Bournemouth East (Mr Ellwood), issued a press statement strongly condemning the attack. We have called on the Israeli authorities to ensure that those responsible for this crime are brought swiftly to justice.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2015-09-24T15:41:07.28Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418608/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418608/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418608/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-09-14","West Bank: Arson","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what contact, if any, Ministers and diplomats have had with the Dawabsha family following the death of three members of that family in an arson attack in Duma village in July.","false","Biography information for Baroness Tonge",,"Baroness Tonge","HL2200"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418609","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-09-24","<p>We assess that government funding per student for Christian schools has fallen by approximately 50% during the last five years. Officials from our Embassy in Tel Aviv raised this issue with the Israeli Ministry of Education in the summer.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2015-09-24T15:41:32.957Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418609/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418609/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418609/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-09-14","Israel: Church Schools","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of the current differences in the levels of funding between Christian schools and other schools in Israel.","false","Biography information for The Lord Bishop of Coventry",,"The Lord Bishop of Coventry","HL2201"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418610","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-09-24","<p>We condemn all extremist violence, including those attacks against religious buildings. Whilst most ‘price tag’ attacks have taken place in the Occupied Palestinian Territories, we are aware that on 18 June the Benedictine Church of the Multiplication at Tabgha, on the Sea of Galilee, was set on fire and vandalised with graffiti. Officials from our Embassy in Tel Aviv raised this at the time with the Israeli Foreign Ministry and National Security Council. Although it did not occur in Israel, it is worth noting the arson attack that took place in February on a Greek Orthodox seminary in East Jerusalem, again with inflammatory graffiti. We are also aware that Muslim and Jewish holy places are desecrated and we unequivocally condemn all such incidents. On 10 September the Prime Minister, my right hon. Friend the Member for Witney (Mr Cameron), and the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, my right hon. Friend the Member for Runnymede and Weybridge (Mr Hammond), raised their concerns for peace in the region with Israeli Prime Minister Netanyahu.</p><p> </p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2015-09-24T15:41:48.367Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418610/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418610/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418610/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-09-14","Israel: Churches","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what is their current assessment of the number of "price tag" attacks on church property in Israel.","false","Biography information for The Lord Bishop of Coventry",,"The Lord Bishop of Coventry","HL2202"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418611","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-09-22","<p>In England, the Environment Agency has an extensive monitoring network over both surface and groundwaters, to comply with European groundwater legislation (2006/118/EC) and requirements under the EU Priority Substances Directive (2008/105/EC and its update, 2013/39/EU). It monitors surface waters for priority substances (set at EU level), and also certain other chemicals of a national, but not European, concern.</p><p> </p><p>The Environment Agency are developing a programme to monitor priority substances that accumulate in biota (e.g. in fish or shellfish) at a number of freshwater sites in England.</p><p> </p><p>The Environment Agency is shortly to start contributing to the European-wide surveillance of a number of emerging substances of concern (the watch list) required under Directive 2013/39/EU.<strong> </strong>This monitoring will include the xenoestrogen ethinyloestradiol.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Gardiner of Kimble",,"2015-09-22T16:01:07.79Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418611/answer","Biography information for Lord Gardiner of Kimble","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418611/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418611/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-09-14","Water: Pollution","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what is the current state of the monitoring in the United Kingdom of the industrial chemicals present in groundwater and river water, in particular pseudo-oestrogens (xenoestrogens) and those substances itemised in Directive 2008/105/EC.","false","Biography information for Viscount Hanworth",,"Viscount Hanworth","HL2203"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418612","Home Office","false","2015-09-22","<p>There have been two recent changes to the level of the cash allowances provided to destitute asylum seekers to cover their essential living needs.</p><p>With effect from 6 April, the allowance provided to asylum seekers without dependants was raised to £36.95 per week (from £36.62).</p><p>Since 10 August a standard payment of £36.95 per week has been provided for each person in a family group (the asylum seeker and any dependants). This resulted in a reduction in the total allowance provided to asylum seekers with children. The change was made because a review of the support system showed that the allowances previously provided exceeded the amount necessary to cover essential living needs.</p><p>There are no plans to reverse either of these changes. The Government generally reviews the level of the allowances each year and plans to do so again in 2016.</p>",,"Lord Bates",,"2015-09-22T15:39:42.76Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418612/answer","Biography information for Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418612/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418612/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-09-14","Asylum: Finance","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether they plan to reverse the cut imposed with effect from August on asylum support, in the light of the fact that this has been frozen since 2011; and whether they will introduce special rates for children under section 95 of the Immigration and Asylum Act 1999.","false","Biography information for Lord Hylton",,"Lord Hylton","HL2204"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418613","Home Office","false","2015-09-21","<p>The Government has no plans to change its policy on the application of the Dublin and Eurodac Regulations. Guidance to officials is under review in order to reflect current organisational structures and wider departmental procedures: an updated version will be published once the review has been completed.</p>",,"Lord Bates",,"2015-09-21T15:37:58.233Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418613/answer","Biography information for Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418613/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418613/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-09-14","Asylum","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether they will issue fresh guidance on the Dublin III Agreement concerning asylum applicants, in particular about family reunions.","false","Biography information for Lord Hylton",,"Lord Hylton","HL2205"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418614","Home Office","false","2015-09-22","<p>The consultation document on reforming support for failed asylum seekers published on 4 August referred to the estimated 15,000 failed asylum seekers and their dependants who were in receipt of support under section 95 or section 4 of the Immigration and Asylum Act 1999 at 31 March 2015. It set out proposals for transitional arrangements for these cases, under which that support would remain available, subject to the use of existing powers under which it can be discontinued. A summary of the consultation and the Government’s response to it will be published in due course.</p>",,"Lord Bates",,"2015-09-22T15:40:01.793Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418614/answer","Biography information for Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418614/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418614/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-09-14","Asylum: Finance","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government on what grounds their consultation on reforming support for failed asylum seekers proposes to remove all support from some 15,000 asylum applicants who are not able to produce sufficient evidence to sustain their cases; what assessment they have made of the likelihood that such people will be removed or returned to their countries of origin; and whether they plan to publish a summary of the consultation and their response to it.","false","Biography information for Lord Hylton",,"Lord Hylton","HL2206"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418615","Department for International Development","false","2015-09-23","<p>The statement from the European Commission is consistent with UK policy.</p>",,"Baroness Verma",,"2015-09-23T15:33:35.57Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418615/answer","Biography information for Baroness Verma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418615/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418615/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2015-09-14","Armed Conflict: Sexual Offences","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether the European Commission’s statement on 11 September affirming that female war rape victims must have access to the full range of sexual and reproductive health services including abortion is in accordance with United Kingdom government policy.","false","Biography information for Lord Lester of Herne Hill",,"Lord Lester of Herne Hill","HL2207"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418616","Home Office","false","2015-09-22","<p>International students are included in net migration statistics that are produced by the independent Office for National Statistics (ONS). In line with the internationally agreed UN definition, these statistics define a migrant as someone changing their normal place of residence for more than a year. Students are therefore included in the same way as other migrants. Other countries, such as the United States, Canada, and Australia also include students in their net migration figures. Like other migrants, students who stay for longer than 12 months have an impact on communities, infrastructure and services while they are here, so it is right that they are included in the net migration count. The ONS estimates that in the year ending March 2015 there was a difference of 96,000 in the number of non-EU students coming to and leaving the UK. Therefore student emigration, or the lack of it, is a key driver of overall net migration.</p>",,"Lord Bates",,"2015-09-22T15:40:13.167Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418616/answer","Biography information for Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418616/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418616/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-09-14","Overseas Students: Immigration Controls","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether they have plans to exclude overseas students in institutions of further education from their net migration target.","false","Biography information for Lord Lexden",,"Lord Lexden","HL2208"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418617","Northern Ireland Office","false","2015-09-18","<p>The disclosure of information relating to decisions made by the Parades Commission for Northern Ireland is an operational matter for the Commission acting independently of Government.</p><p>The Noble Lord may wish to write to the Parades Commission directly on this matter.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Dunlop",,"2015-09-18T13:17:58.907Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418617/answer","Biography information for Lord Dunlop","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418617/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418617/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2015-09-14","Parades Commission: Freedom of Information","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether all the material used in making determinations by the Northern Irish Parades Commission is subject to disclosure under the Freedom of Information Act 2000, and if not, why not.","false","Biography information for Lord Laird",,"Lord Laird","HL2209"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418618","Northern Ireland Office","false","2015-09-18","<p>As the Noble Lord is aware, the involvement of the Irish Government in cross-party talks is in accordance with the established three-stranded approach to Northern Ireland affairs and the 1998 Belfast Agreement. This provides that Northern Ireland’s internal arrangements are for the Northern Ireland parties and the United Kingdom Government alone to decide. A commitment always to stand by that principle was contained in the Government’s Northern Ireland Manifesto at the General Election.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Dunlop",,"2015-09-18T12:08:46.607Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418618/answer","Biography information for Lord Dunlop","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418618/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418618/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2015-09-14","Belfast Agreement","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether the Belfast Agreement 1998 provides for a role for the government of the Republic of Ireland in Strand One talks where the discussions are about Northern Irish internal affairs.","false","Biography information for Lord Laird",,"Lord Laird","HL2210"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418619","HM Treasury","false","2015-09-21","<p>No specific assessment has been made of the loss of revenue specifically due to fuel laundering in South Armagh to the UK each year.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The government is committed to reducing revenue loss due to fuel duty fraud and HM Revenue and Customs works closely with the Revenue Commissioners in the Republic of Ireland and others to fight fuel fraud on a wide range of fronts. This includes regular exchange of information, joint operational activity and the recent implementation of an improved new marker for rebated fuel (which was also introduced in the Republic of Ireland).</p><p> </p>",,"Lord O'Neill of Gatley",,"2015-09-21T11:49:47.917Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418619/answer","Biography information for Lord O'Neill of Gatley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418619/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418619/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-09-14","Fuels: Tax Evasion","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how much duty has been lost in each of the last five years as a result of fuel laundering in South Armagh.","false","Biography information for Lord Laird",,"Lord Laird","HL2211"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418620","Department for Transport","false","2015-09-17","<p>There are already a number of measures in place to control motorcycle noise with manufacturers required to meet strict noise limits. We expect the European Commission to undertake a study of noise from new motorcycles and to make proposals for tougher limits that will apply from 2020. The Department for Transport will take an active role in future discussions, with the European Commission and Member States.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon",,"2015-09-17T11:40:11.027Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418620/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418620/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418620/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-09-14","Motorcycles: Noise","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether they have any plans to reduce the noise of motorbikes on public roads.","false","Biography information for Lord Laird",,"Lord Laird","HL2212"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418621","Cabinet Office","false","2015-09-25","<p>Statistics on average days lost across the Civil Service are collected and published by the Cabinet Office on a quarterly basis.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Year ending</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Northern Ireland Office</strong></p><p><strong>AWDL per staff year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Civil Service</strong></p><p><strong>AWDL per staff year</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>31 March 2010</p></td><td><p>8.8</p></td><td><p>8.8</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>31 March 2011</p></td><td><p>12.1</p></td><td><p>8.2</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>31 March 2012</p></td><td><p>10.3</p></td><td><p>7.7</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>31 March 2013</p></td><td><p>3.2</p></td><td><p>7.6</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>31 March 2014</p></td><td><p>6.4</p></td><td><p>7.3</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>31 March 2015</p></td><td><p>5.9</p></td><td><p>7.4</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>The Civil Service actively manages sickness absence and we continually review our progress. We strive to improve health and wellbeing at work for our staff and this remains a priority</p><p> </p><p>The Average Working Days Lost (AWDL) per staff year in the Northern Ireland Office has reduced from 8.8, for the year ending 31 March in 2010, to 5.9, for the same period in 2015.</p><p> </p><p>The Average Working Days Lost (AWDL) per staff year in the Civil Service has reduced from 8.8, for the year ending 31 March in 2010 to 7.4 for the year ending 31 March 2015.</p><p> </p><p>These statistics demonstrate that we have made significant progress in reducing sickness absence in the Northern Ireland Office and the Civil Service as a whole. We are continuing to work with both line managers and staff to address absence issues.</p>",,"Lord Bridges of Headley",,"2015-09-25T11:14:22.207Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418621/answer","Biography information for Lord Bridges of Headley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418621/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418621/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2015-09-14","Civil Servants: Sick Leave","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what is the average number of days lost through sickness in the Northern Ireland Office, and in the civil service as a whole, over the last five years.","false","Biography information for Lord Laird",,"Lord Laird","HL2213"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418622","Attorney General","false","2015-09-17","<p>Options are being considered for the future of the Fund, consistent with its object of extinguishing or reducing the national debt. A proposal will be set out in due course.</p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright","10237","2015-09-17T15:53:51.313Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418622/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418622/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418622/answer",,,,,"88","Attorney General","Attorney General","2015-09-14","National Fund","1","House of Commons","To ask the Attorney General, what progress he has made on discussions about the future of the National Debt Fund charity; and what steps he is taking to secure legal approval to change the charitable objects of that charity and remove the requirement on it to pay off the whole national debt.","false","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd","10207"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418623","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-09-24","<p>The Student Income and Expenditure Survey which took place earlier this year will report on the finances of HE students in England and Wales. The report is expected to be published in early 2016.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Maintenance support is a contribution to student living costs. However we are increasing the overall cash-in-hand we provide to students to support their cost of living.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2015-09-24T12:31:05.747Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418623/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418623/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418623/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-09-14","Students: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what assessment his Department has made of the adequacy of the level of maintenance support for undergraduate students; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Jim Cunningham","Coventry South","Mr Jim Cunningham","10182"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418624","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-09-17","<p>We have had no such discussions. Operational matters, which include decisions relating to Royal Mail’s postage stamps, are the direct responsibility of the company’s management (subject to an agreed convention and criteria governing the designs of postage stamps carrying an image of The Queen’s head, which are overseen by this Department).</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The company maintains Country Definitives on an ongoing basis and has no current plans to change existing designs or its policy on such stamps. Country Definitives are available on an ongoing basis from post offices in the respective countries, and available direct from Royal Mail.</p><p> </p>","Mid Norfolk","George Freeman",,"2015-09-17T09:39:20.66Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418624/answer","Biography information for George Freeman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418624/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418624/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-09-14","Postage Stamps","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what recent discussions he has had with Royal Mail on the continued issuing of Country definitive postage stamps.","false","Biography information for Patrick Grady","Glasgow North","Patrick Grady","10191"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418625","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-09-22","<p /> <p>We are supporting entrepreneurs and small businesses in many ways and are committed to making sure the UK is the best place in Europe to start and grow a business.</p><p>For example <em>Start-up Loans</em> provide new entrepreneurs with start-up finance and advice. And the <em>Enterprise Finance Guarantee</em> scheme encourages lenders, such as banks, to lend to smaller businesses that would not ordinarily get a loan. The table below shows how much both schemes have lent to small businesses in Suffolk, East of England and England and Wales.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong> </strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Start-Up Loans</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Enterprise Finance Guarantee</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>Suffolk</strong></p></td><td><p>222 Start Up Loans issued totalling £1.04m</p></td><td><p>296 EFG loans issued totalling £27.1m</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>East of England</strong></p></td><td><p>2,096 issued totalling £9.9m</p></td><td><p>2,131 issued totalling £219.2m</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>England and Wales</strong></p></td><td><p>29,736 issued totalling £159.6m.</p><p> </p><p> </p></td><td><p>22,755 issued totalling £2,317.7m</p><p> </p><p> </p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>The Government is also supporting small firms through grant funding provided by Innovate UK to support science and technology innovations that will grow the economy. In 2014/15 around 60% of Innovate UK’s funding went to small &amp; medium sized enterprises. In the same period expenditure to micro and small enterprises in the East of England was £18.8m.</p><p>Growth hubs across England make sure that small businesses can access this support and other local and private sector support available to start and grow a business. There are currently 29 growth hubs delivering business support to around 79% of the registered business population. The remaining hubs are due to roll out across England by March 2016. The New Anglia Growth Hub provides support to businesses in the Suffolk area and has helped over 3,000 businesses and created 450 jobs. Four hubs currently provide support to businesses in the East of England area.</p><p>And the New Anglia Local Enterprise Partnership has secured over £220m as part of their Growth Deal to help transform the economy of Norfolk and Suffolk. This money will fund a range of initiatives including road improvements, building new innovation centres and providing grants to help businesses grow.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry","10150","2015-09-22T13:34:04.77Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418625/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418625/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/418625/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-09-14","New Businesses: Government Assistance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what steps are being taken to support entrepreneurs in (a) Suffolk, (b) the East of England and (c) England and Wales.","false","Biography information for Jo Churchill","Bury St Edmunds","Jo Churchill","10187"
